5 A BILL
6 TO BE ENTITLED
7 AN ACT
8
9 Relating to campaign finance; to add Section 17-5-7.3
10 to the Code of Alabama 1975, to authorize campaign funds to be
11 used for certain security measures to protect the safety of a
12 candidate, an elected official, or his or her immediate family
13 or staff; and to allow legislators who used campaign funds to
14 purchase furnishings for their offices at the State House on
15 South Union Street before a certain date to dispose of the
16 property in preparation for demolition of the building.
17 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
18 Section 1. Section 17-5-7.3 is added to the Code of
19 Alabama 1975, to read as follows:
20 §17-5-7.3
21 (a) In addition to the use of campaign contributions
22 for the purposes listed in Section 17-5-7, campaign
23 contributions may be used to pay, or reimburse the state or
24 any county or municipality, for security expenses to protect
25 the safety of a candidate, an elected official, or an
26 immediate family or staff member of a candidate or an elected
27 official. For purposes of this section, "security expenses"
28 include all of the following:
Page 1

include all of the following:
XD1AL77-1 02/25/2026 PMG (H) HSE 2026-132
House Ethics and Campaign Finance Reported
Substitute for SB230
29 (1) Reasonable costs of cybersecurity such as data
30 removal services that find and remove personal information of
31 a candidate, elected official, or immediate family or staff
32 member of the candidate or elected official from data brokers
33 and websites, and other online sources.
34 (2) Reasonable costs of installing and monitoring
35 nonstructural security devices, including home security
36 hardware, locks, alarm systems, motion detectors, and security
37 cameras, provided the security devices are intended to provide
38 security and not to improve or increase the value of the
39 property.
40 (3) Reasonable costs of security personnel for a
41 candidate, elected official, or immediate family or staff
42 member of the candidate or elected official.
43 (b) Any device or other item purchased and installed
44 pursuant to subsection (a) which is permanently attached to
45 the property of a candidate, elected official, or immediate
46 family or staff member of the candidate or elected official is
47 exempt from the liquidation provisions of Section 17-5-7.2.
48 (c) Nothing in this section shall be construed to
49 require the state, a county, or a municipality to provide
50 security solely based on this section.
51 Section 2. Notwithstanding Section 17-5-7.2, Code of
52 Alabama 1975, a member of the Legislature who, on or before
53 January 1, 2026, acquired property described in Section
54 17-5-7.2(a), Code of Alabama 1975, to furnish his or her
55 office in the Alabama State House located on South Union
56 Street in Montgomery, may, in preparation for the demolition
Page 2

